<recipe>
<title>
Slow Cooker Sweet Potato Casserole Recipe
</title>
<details>
PREP TIME: 20 minutes
COOK TIME: 4 hours
TOTAL TIME: 4 hours 20 minutes
</details>
<ingredients>
CASSEROLE
1/2 c . brown sugar packed
3 T . butter melted
1 T . pumpkin pie spice
1 T . vanilla extract
3-4 lb . sweet potatoes peeled and cut into 1/2-inch cubes
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Grease a slow cooker (I used a 5-quart) with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl toss together brown sugar, butter, spice, vanilla, and cut sweet potatoes.
Add sweet potato mixture to slow cooker.
In a medium bowl, mix together oats, brown sugar, flour, cinnamon, and melted butter for the topping.
Spread topping evenly over slow cooker.
Cover, and cook on high for 3-4 hours, or until sweet potatoes are fork tender.
Sprinkle with pecans just before serving.
</instructions>
</recipe>
